article.headline: George Mason defeats American U 63-60
article.story: FAIRFAX, Va. -- Bryon Allen scored 20 points Friday night to lead George Mason to a 63-60 win over American University. Sherrod Wright, who led the Patriots in scoring last season, made a layup with 2:54 left to give them a 58-57 lead. American missed 3-pointers on its next two possessions and Allen answered with a layup off a fast break to put the Patriots (1-0) up by three. American (0-1) never got closer. Allen went 5 for 10 from the floor and made 9 of 10 free throws. Wright finished with 13 points. Jesse Reed had 15 points and three 3-pointers to lead American University. John Schoof, who returns as the team's leading scorer, went 3 for 11 for 8 points. This was the 41st game in the rivalry but the first time the teams have met since 2005-2006.
